<HEADLINE> Immigration Problems Sideline Vorbe  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Sebastien Vorbe's regular season debut
with the Los Angeles Galaxy will be delayed because of immigration
problems.
</P>
<P>
   Vorbe, a Haitian national team midfielder, signed with the
Galaxy on Tuesday and hoped to play Saturday against the New
York-New Jersey MetroStars in East Rutherford, N.J. But Vorbe has
had problems with getting a work permit, a team spokesman said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   It was uncertain when Vorbe, 23, would be able to play for the
Galaxy. Further complicating matters is Vorbe's commitment to play
for Haiti in World Cup qualifiers in May.
</P>
<P>
   Vorbe played with the Galaxy during the preseason and scored the
winning goal in a 2-1 victory over Talleres de Cordoba of the
Argentine First Division on March 8 in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
   Vorbe played for Florida International in 1997 and '98, and
scored nine goals in 37 matches.
</P>
