<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Open Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were higher in early trading today.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 32 points in the early
going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a
3-to-2 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was ahead 60 points and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index was up five points.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say with Wall Street able to basically stare down
Thursday's strong economic news, the market looks good to go.
</P>
<P>
   Market-watchers are encouraged by Wall Street's ability to rally
back from early trouble.
</P>
