<HEADLINE> Benelli To Build Renault Scooters  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PESARO, Italy (AP) -- Benelli, an Italian motorcycle and motor
scooter manufacturer, has agreed to build a line of scooters for
Renault that will bear the French automaker's name.
</P>
<P>
   ''We still don't know how many units will be produced in total.
It's for Renault to decide according to their sales plan,''
Benelli's president, Andrea Merloni, said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Benelli will build the scooters at its Pesaro factory in central
Italy, Merloni said.
</P>
<P>
   Didier Marsaud, spokesman for Renault SA in Boulogne, France
refused to say how much the agreement was worth and would not
specify the number of vehicles Benelli will produce on behalf of
Renault.
</P>
<P>
   Renault will take sole charge of worldwide distribution for the
scooters, which will make their appearance in the first half of
2001, said Marsaud.
</P>
</TEXT>
