<HEADLINE> Treasury Bond Prices Are Mixed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Treasury bond prices were mixed at midday.
</P>
<P>
   The price of the Treasury's main 30-year bond was down 14-32
point, or $4.37{ per $1,000 in face value, around midday, while its
yield rose to 5.95 percent from 5.98 percent late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   But prices on shorter-term securities were down by as much as
5-32 point.
</P>
<P>
   Yields on three-month Treasury bills rose to 5.79 percent as the
discount gained 0.06 percentage point to 5.64 percent. Six-month
yields rose to 6.08 percent as the discount rose 0.03 percentage
point to 5.83 percent. One-year yields were quoted at 6.13 percent
as the discount held at 5.83 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the
discount is the interest at which they are sold.
</P>
