<HEADLINE> NBC Extends 'ER' Through 2004  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The prognosis is good for Noah Wyle and the
staff of ''ER.''
</P>
<P>
   NBC said Friday it has extended the show's run through the
2003-04 season.
</P>
<P>
   TV viewers ''can rest assured that television's favorite doctors
of all time will be making house calls at NBC for at least the next
four years,'' said Garth Ancier, president of NBC Entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   ''ER'' premiered in 1994 and has been the No. 1 drama on
television for six consecutive seasons.
</P>
<P>
   While former stars Sherry Stringfield and George Clooney have
checked out and Julianna Margulies is leaving at the end of this
season, original cast members Wyle, Anthony Edwards and Eriq La
Salle have said they'll stick with the show.
</P>
</TEXT>
