<HEADLINE> European Stocks End Mostly Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- A strong showing by the technology, media and
telecom sectors, combined with resilience on Wall Street, boosted
most European stocks Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of European companies rose 6.63
points, or 1.7 percent, to 392.60, while the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx
Index climbed 10.16 points, or 2.4 percent, to 438.58.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index was up 132 points at 5,304.0,
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index rose 105.6 points to 5,094.5.
</P>
<P>
   Technology stocks were propelled higher by
stronger-than-expected results from Swedish telecom equipment maker
Ericsson. The sector ticker ended the day up 5.5 percent, or 57.1
points, at 1091.7.
</P>
<P>
   Morgan Stanley Dean Witter European Equity Strategist Richard
Davidson said the strong earnings from Ericsson showed that
technology stocks continued to represent good value.
</P>
<P>
   ''Technology is cheap,'' Davidson said. ''It is not a sentiment
change. It's (movement) is based on fundamental results.''
</P>
<P>
   Older economy sectors also posted reasonable gains, and analysts
cited the benefits of a slumping euro on the earnings of big
corporate exporters.
</P>
<P>
   In Paris the CAC-40 Index rose 2.8 percent, or 171.86 points, to
6,491.72, buoyed by a strong showing from telecom giant Alcatel on
speculation that a major deal would be announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   German shares ended 2.7 percent higher, led by Siemens, as
strong gains on New York's Nasdaq market helped the Xetra recover
Thursday's losses. The DAX climbed 192 points or 2.7 percent to
7,414 points, with techs performing well, while auto stocks posted
losses.
</P>
<P>
   In Milan the Mibtel was up 494 points or 1.6 percent to 31,083,
while in London the FTSE 100 rose 148.1 points or 2.3 percent to
6,327.4
</P>
<P>
   Sweden's blue-chip OMX index closed up 25.80 points, or 1.8
percent, at 1,429.61 while the general index, ther SXG, ended up
106.31 points, or 1.7 percent, at 6,203.20.
</P>
