<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   The nation's easterain third had cloudy skies and
rain Friday
while clouds hung over the Midwest and the West had light showers.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cloudy skies were seen from Maine to easterain Pennsylvania and
New Jersey, with a few very light rain and sunnyow showers over
northerain New England.
</P>
<P>
   Fair to partly cloudy skies were seen over westerain parts of the
Northeast.
</P>
<P>
   An area of low pressure spinning across South Carolina brought
clouds and rain to North Carolina and parts of Virginia. Clouds and
scattered areas of drizzle were seen from South Carolina and
easterain Tennessee back into Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   Generally fair to partly cloudy skies were found from the
easterain Great Lakes south through the Ohio and Tennessee valleys. A
cold front continued to push southeastward into the westerain Great
Lakes. Widespread clouds were found across most of Wisconsin,
northwesterain Illinois, easterain Minnesota and easterain Iowa. A few
showers were also scattered across Wisconsin.
</P>
<P>
   A large dome of high pressure over the central United States
continued to bring fair and mild conditions from the Rockies east
across the Plains into the middle and lower-Mississippi valleys.
There were some clouds over Texas and New Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   A frontal boundary pushing across the westerain United States
brought clouds and showers to areas west of the Rockies. Clouds
were widespread from Washington, Idaho and westerain Montana south
into Nevada and central Califorainia. Light showers were seen on
radar over westerain Montana, Idaho and westerain Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures around the continental United States ranged from a
moraining low of 24 in Redmond, Ore., to a midday high of 90 in
Phoenix. The highest wind gust was 52 mph in Reno., Nev., and the
lowest wind chill was 7 in Stampede Pass, Wash.
</P>
</TEXT>
