<HEADLINE> Minister Sentenced in Teacher Attack  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- A minister accused of assaulting a teacher for
giving his daughter a D-minus on her report card was sentenced to
2{ years in prison Friday.
</P>
<P>
   A jury convicted Dale Robinson, 36, of assault and battery and
disturbing the peace. Judge Rosalind Miller gave Robinson the
maximum penalty for assault and battery and ordered him to serve 10
additional days on the disturbing-the-peace charge.
</P>
<P>
   Teacher Antonio Centeio lost several teeth and suffered eye
injuries and a broken jaw when Robinson, a 6-foot-8 former high
school basketball star, attacked him last year. Prosecutors said
the attack came after Robinson's daughter brought home near-failing
grades on her report card.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson, a minister and youth counselor in the city's Roxbury
section, allegedly told Centeio, ''This isn't over yet'' after the
attack.
</P>
<P>
   ''For any parent, a minister nonetheless, to enter a school and
strike a teacher because of a bad grade is deplorable,'' District
Attorney Ralph C. Martin said in a statement. ''Parents are
supposed to set examples to which their children should aspire.''
</P>
</TEXT>
