<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States 4, Guatemala 0  </HEADLINE>
By BARRY WILNER, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- With an offensive burst rarely seen from an
American team, the United States stormed into the Sydney Olympics
soccer field Friday night by routing Guatemala 4-0.
</P>
<P>
   Getting two goals in the opening eight minutes and three in the
first 22, the American under-23 squad easily won its CONCACAF
semifinal game.
</P>
<P>
   The United States joined Honduras, which defeated Mexico 5-4 in
a shootout after a 0-0 tie in the opener, in Sunday's final. Both
teams earned berths at the 2000 Olympics in September.
</P>
<P>
   Few American soccer teams have displayed the explosiveness this
group showed against Guatemala. Only 46 seconds after kickoff, on
the first U.S. possession, Chris Albright headed a long free kick
by Peter Vagenas toward the middle of the penalty area. John
O'Brien, running full speed, sent a rocket of a shot over the arms
of goalie Luis Molina.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd of 12,299, some of whom were still settling into their
seats, erupted in noise as O'Brien did a somersault following his
goal.
</P>
<P>
   That was just the start.
</P>
<P>
   After U.S. defender Ramiro Corrales made a long clear from in
front of his net during a scramble in the eighth minute, Albright
took the ball in the clear. His left-footed shot was deflected by
Molina, but it fell right to Josh Wolff, who tapped it into an open
net as Molina looked around for his defense.
</P>
<P>
   The Guatemalan defense was nowhere to be seen on the third goal,
either.
</P>
<P>
   Ben Olsen, the only member of the under-23 team who also plays
regularly for the main national squad -- players must be under 23
years old to play in Olympic qualifying -- set it up. He rolled the
ball to his right to Wolff, whose cross into the middle was
intentionally ignored by Albright, who knew Landon Donovan was
behind him. Donovan tapped it home in the 22nd minute.
</P>
<P>
   With the Guatemalans demoralized, the Americans kept up their
unrelenting attack. But they either misfired or Molina made a
difficult save to keep it 3-0, although the hosts had a 19-2 shot
advantage.
</P>
<P>
   The second half was marred by fouls and five yellow-card
cautions. But the Americans never let Guatemala press the attack in
earning their third straight qualifying shutout.
</P>
<P>
   Donovan scored his second goal in the final minute of the game.
</P>
<P>
   At the end, the U.S. players carried a banner around the field
saying ''Thank You Hershey, Olympics 2000.'' Several American
players were draped in U.S. flags.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier in the six-nation tournament, the United States beat
Honduras 3-0 and tied Canada 0-0.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-28-00 2223 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000428.0252 </DOCNO>
