<HEADLINE> U.S. Journalist Detained in Vietnam  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Tucker Carlson, a reporter for the
conservative magazine The Weekly Standard and a CNN political
commentator, was detained briefly by Vietnamese authorities in Ho
Chi Minh City, who questioned his travel documents, a spokeswoman
for the magazine said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Carlson, 30, was part of a group of reporters covering the
Vietnam visit of Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., who was a prisoner of
war for over five years. When Carlson attempted to board a plane
back to the United States on Friday, Vietnamese officials accused
him of being in their country illegally because he lacked a proper
exit visa.
</P>
<P>
   A State Department spokesman said Friday night that Vietnamese
authorities had told them Carlson was free to leave the country as
soon as he arranged transportation. Carolyn Wimmer of the Weekly
Standard said the magazine had not been able to reach him.
</P>
</TEXT>
