<HEADLINE> Chronology of Pa. Shooting Spree  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Chronology of shootings in suburban Pittsburgh based
on reports
to police and firefighters:
<TEXT>
<P>
   1:43 p.m. -- House fire reported in Mount Lebanon, a Pittsburgh
suburb. Firefighters find a woman's body at the house.
</P>
<P>
   1:55 p.m. -- Two shot at Indian grocery store in Carnegie. About
the same time, shots reported fired at two nearby synagogues in
Carnegie and near Mount Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
   2:30 p.m. -- Two employees shot at Chinese restaurant in McKees
Rocks.
</P>
<P>
   3 p.m. -- Man shot at karate school in Monaca.
</P>
<P>
   3:15 p.m. -- Suspect Richard Baumhammers, 34, arrested in
Ambridge.
</P>
